metadata.name: Pig-nosed turtle
metadata.description:
(Pig-nosed turtle, Fly river turtle)
In 1979, flying turtles were considered extremely rare and expensive. Worldwide, there are only 5 occupants in 5 countries, but at present can be bred in Indonesia,
very close to extinction Due to the threat of habitat and being adopted as pets, infested in rivers, canals or lakes that are not very deep. on the island of Papua New Guinea and Australia in the north They can eat a wide variety of food, both plants and animals, or carrion because they are turtles with poor eyesight.
